               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390617-name-669" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-669" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-669" type="surname" value="WILSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-669" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN WILSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to John Davies and another, linen-drapers in Chiswell-street. On the evening of the 25th of May, the prisoner and another person came in—I was serving a lady who made a remark to me, which made me look at the prisoner—I saw him putting something into</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183906170082"></xptr>
               <p>his trowsers—he went out, I followed him—he had got two doors off—I saw something in his trowsers, and Haseldine took the shawl from him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390617-name-670" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-670" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-670" type="surname" value="HASELDINE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-670" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS HASELDINE</persName>
                  </hi>. I was passing—Wilson had the prisoner by the collar—I saw the fringe hanging out of his trowsers—I pulled it out, and it was this shawl.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I picked it up outside the house.</p>
